ey are dried up, they are gone away from men.","year":-1520},{"id":"reckMtAlMDJOEuMfu","ref":"Job.28.5","text":"As for the earth, out of it cometh bread: and under it is turned up as it were fire.","year":-1520},{"id":"rec0entV1hGDh83KM","ref":"Job.28.6","text":"The stones of it are the place of sapphires: and it hath dust of gold.","year":-1520},{"id":"rec5jDbG1ykP1OuWx","ref":"Job.28.7","text":"There is a path which no fowl knoweth, and which the vulture’s eye hath not seen:","year":-1520},{"id":"recWHoldycxaLOaaT","ref":"Job.28.8","text":"The lion’s whelps have not trodden it, nor the fierce lion passed by it.","year":-1520}]}
